Practice Set 2 – Strings

1️ Ask a name and print it in uppercase and lowercase.
print(name.upper())
print(name.lower())

&&
name = input("Enter Your Name Here : ")
print(name.upper())
print(name.lower())
print(name[::-5])
rev = name[::-1]
print(rev)


2️⃣ Print first and last character of a string.
print(name[0] + name[-1])
or
print("First character:", name[0])
print("Last character:", name[-1])

3️⃣ Reverse a string.
Example:  Python → nohtyP
name = input("Enter your name: ")
name1 = name[::-1]
print(name1)

4️⃣ Count characters excluding spaces.
name = input("Enter name: ")
count = len(name.replace(" ", ""))
print("Characters (excluding spaces):", count)

or
name = input("Enter your name : ")
count = name.replace(" ", "")
print(len(count))

5️⃣ Replace spaces with underscores.
name = input("Enter your name : ")
result = name.replace(" ", "_")
print(result)

6️⃣ Check if a word is palindrome.
Example:  madam → palindrome
name = input("Enter a word: ")

rev = name[::-1]

if name == rev:
    print(name, "is a palindrome")
else:
    print(name, "is not a palindrome")
or
word = input("Enter a word: ")

if word == word[::-1]:
    print("Palindrome")
else:
    print("Not a palindrome")
